column168: RESPONDER ARRIVED TO LEAKING HAZMAT PACKAGE WAS NEAR REAR OF TRAILER WITH ARROWS UP AND LEAKING OUT BOTTOM.

THE DESIGNATED RESPONDER WAS NOTIFIED ABOUT A LEAKING HAZMAT IN THE PRELOAD OPERATION. WEARING THE APPROPRIATE PPE DOMINIC COLORAD, THE DESIGNATED RESPONDER WENT TO THE LOCATION OF THE SPILL FOR CLEAN UP. PLACING THE LEAKER IN A LINED SPILL TRAY AND UTILIZING THE DECISION TREE AND RESPONSE SHEET. THE RESPONDER THEN RETURNED WITH THE PACKAGE/DEBRIS TO THE DAMAGE CAGE FOR FURTHER INSPECTION.
